Intentional local patches (re-apply after any re-vendor; each marked
with a "// d9mt" comment in the file):

1. src/util/util_env.cpp
   #ifdef __APPLE__ uses the single-argument macOS
   pthread_setname_np(name) (applies to calling thread) instead of
   pthread_setname_np(pthread_self(), name). macOS port fix.

2. src/util/util_small_vector.h
   In pick_capacity, casts (n - 1) to uint64_t before bit::lzcnt
   because size_t is unsigned long on macOS and is ambiguous between
   the uint32_t/uint64_t lzcnt overloads. macOS compile fix.

3. src/dxvk/dxvk_unbound.h
   Local d9mt extension (matches no upstream ref): adds dummy
   imageViewDescriptor(VkImageViewType, bool storage) and
   bufferViewDescriptor(bool storage) returning const DxvkDescriptor*,
   plus m_image1D/2D/3D, an array of 2*(VK_IMAGE_VIEW_TYPE_CUBE_ARRAY+1)
   image views, sampled/storage buffer views, and
   createImage/createImages/createBufferViews helpers — fallback dummy
   resources for unbound bindings on devices without the nullDescriptor
   feature (the Metal backend). Written against v2.7.1's DxvkDescriptor
   API; conceptually backports the pre-2022 upstream dummy-resource
   feature (removed upstream in 6f5ae58c) but is not a copy of any
   upstream version. A matching dxvk_unbound.cpp implementation will be
   needed.

4. src/dxvk/dxvk_dummy_frag.h
   Local addition, not in any tag's tree: pre-generated SPIR-V
   uint32_t array for upstream's src/dxvk/shaders/dxvk_dummy_frag.frag
   (upstream compiles it with glslang at build time). Checked in so the
   mingw build does not need glslang. Keep as-is.

